    "body": "Ok sorry I'm just getting around to this today. I believe that this is actually intended behavior for Geth. To check this, I made a simple test contract:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\ncontract Reverter {\r\n    function doRevert() public {\r\n        revert(\"THIS IS A REVERT\");\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nAnd ran the following test against a local (standard Ethereum) geth node:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nconst hre = require('hardhat')\r\nconst { expect } = require('chai')\r\n\r\ndescribe('Reverter', () => {\r\n    it('should revert', async () => {\r\n        const factory = await hre.ethers.getContractFactory('Reverter')\r\n        const contract = await factory.deploy()\r\n\r\n        await expect(\r\n            contract.doRevert({\r\n                gasLimit: 5000000\r\n            })\r\n        ).to.be.revertedWith('THIS IS A REVERT')\r\n    })\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nHere's the result:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  Reverter\r\n    1) should revert\r\n\r\n\r\n  0 passing (130ms)\r\n  1 failing\r\n\r\n  1) Reverter\r\n       should revert:\r\n\r\n      AssertionError: Expected transaction to be reverted\r\n      + expected - actual\r\n\r\n      -Transaction NOT reverted.\r\n      +Transaction reverted.\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, this test *does* pass when running via `hardhat-evm`:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  Reverter\r\n    âœ“ should revert (448ms)\r\n\r\n\r\n  1 passing (451ms)\r\n```",
